Class DistributedRelay

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.tomp2p.relay.DistributedRelay
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PeerMapChangeListener

    public class DistributedRelay
extends Object
implements PeerMapChangeListener
    The relay manager is responsible for setting up and maintaining connections to relay peers and contains all information about the relays.
    Author:
    Raphael Voellmy, Thomas Bocek, Nico Rutishauser

      • setupRelays

        public DistributedRelay setupRelays(List<PeerAddress> relays)
        Sets up relay connections to other peers. The number of relays to set up is determined by PeerAddress#MAX_RELAYS or passed to the constructor of this class. It is important that we call this after we bootstrapped and have recent information in our peer map.
        Returns:
        RelayFuture containing a DistributedRelay instance
